Job Portal Backend (Express + MongoDB)

This is the backend for a job portal application built using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB.
It provides APIs for managing users, companies, jobs, and applications, with authentication and cookie handling.

🚀 Features

User authentication & management

Company management

Job postings & listings

Application management

MongoDB connection with Mongoose

CORS enabled for frontend integration

Serves frontend (React/Vite build) from frontend/dist

📂 Project Structure
project/
│── routes/
│   ├── userroutes.js
│   ├── companyroutes.js
│   ├── jobroutes.js
│   └── applicationroutes.js
│
│── utils/
│   └── db.js         # MongoDB connection
│
│── frontend/         # React frontend build (served by backend)
│
│── server.js         # Main Express app
│── .env              # Environment variables
│── package.json

⚙️ Installation

Clone the repository

git clone <repo-url>
cd project


Install dependencies

npm install


Install dev dependencies (optional, for hot reload)

npm install --save-dev nodemon

📦 Dependencies

express

cookie-parser

cors

dotenv

mongoose

🔑 Environment Variables

Create a .env file in the root directory with the following:

PORT=8080
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key

▶️ Running the App
Development
npm run dev


(using nodemon)

Production
npm start


Server will run on:

http://localhost:8080

🌐 API Endpoints
Route	Method	Description
/api/v1/user	CRUD	User-related routes
/api/v1/company	CRUD	Company-related routes
/api/v1/job	CRUD	Job-related routes
/api/v1/applications	CRUD	Application routes
📦 Serving Frontend

This backend serves the React (Vite) frontend build:

Place your frontend build inside frontend/dist.

Backend will serve index.html for all routes (app.get('*')).
